266
00:27:02,980 --> 00:27:05,195
He still loves you.

267
00:27:06,007 --> 00:27:10,804
The fact that you're here right now
is already His mercy.

268
00:27:12,770 --> 00:27:17,202
And you know very well
what scholarship you received.

269
00:27:20,250 --> 00:27:22,195
A diocesan scholarship.

270
00:27:24,327 --> 00:27:28,900
Your duty isn't only to study.

271
00:27:30,922 --> 00:27:32,802
While you're here,

272
00:27:33,238 --> 00:27:37,980
I want you to find yourself
and see how you can serve God.

273
00:27:39,637 --> 00:27:42,296
But if you keep behaving like this,

274
00:27:43,656 --> 00:27:46,240
I'll have to ask you to leave the school.

275
00:27:51,225 --> 00:27:52,225
Yes.

276
00:28:01,090 --> 00:28:04,250
Master Phak asked me to bring you
these documents to sign, Father.

277
00:28:05,414 --> 00:28:06,414
Thank you.

278
00:28:06,450 --> 00:28:07,450
You're welcome.

279
00:28:22,054 --> 00:28:24,840
Tanrak, do you know what the painting
"Ticket to Heaven" means?

280
00:28:29,601 --> 00:28:33,100
It tells the story of the path to heaven.

281
00:28:34,130 --> 00:28:39,598
Along the way, beasts devour sinful humans

282
00:28:41,317 --> 00:28:43,200
and tempt people off the path.

283
00:28:49,594 --> 00:28:51,499
I'm leaving Barth in your care.

284
00:28:52,208 --> 00:28:54,299
He needs help right now.

285
00:28:55,081 --> 00:28:58,801
And I believe you can help him.

286
00:29:00,910 --> 00:29:01,910
Yes, Father.

287
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:44,401
Hey, Tanrak,
what are you standing around for?

288
00:30:44,630 --> 00:30:47,202
Hurry up. I need to take a dump,
or we'll be late for class.

289
00:30:55,602 --> 00:30:57,099
Students, salute.

290
00:30:59,188 --> 00:31:00,299
Thank you, sir.

291
00:31:02,950 --> 00:31:07,496
Hey, Master Phak wants us to help
the younger kids on duty this evening.

292
00:31:07,832 --> 00:31:11,197
They just assigned duties,
and they're still kind of confused.

293
00:31:11,764 --> 00:31:12,764
Sure.

294
00:31:13,410 --> 00:31:15,300
They're probably
as lost as you were in Grade 7.

295
00:31:15,750 --> 00:31:16,750
When was I lost?

296
00:31:16,890 --> 00:31:19,050
When you wandered off
to the 60th Anniversary Building.

297
00:31:19,308 --> 00:31:20,479
What were you even doing there alone?

298
00:31:20,503 --> 00:31:22,500
Well, to meet you, apparently.

299
00:31:23,761 --> 00:31:26,201
Yeah, so we were both idiots.

300
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:07,102
How do you spell your name?

301
00:32:09,204 --> 00:32:12,797
Bodin. B-O-D-I-N.

302
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:20,880
And your nickname?

303
00:32:25,414 --> 00:32:27,502
Barth. B-A-R-T-H.

304
00:32:39,616 --> 00:32:42,930
Here. Sign in for homeroom roll call.

305
00:33:44,050 --> 00:33:47,500
Hey, aren't we
supposed to play football today?

306
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:50,500
I know.

307
00:33:51,710 --> 00:33:53,470
That's why I'm playing
basketball right here.

308
00:33:55,102 --> 00:33:56,597
Fine. Suit yourself.

309
00:33:59,397 --> 00:34:00,502
Damn.

310
00:34:02,660 --> 00:34:04,020
I even made the effort to ask him.

311
00:34:15,238 --> 00:34:17,299
Kong, Tanrak, wanna play football?

312
00:34:18,053 --> 00:34:19,053
We're good.

313
00:34:19,647 --> 00:34:20,647
Okay.

314
00:34:34,780 --> 00:34:35,780
Hey, Kong.

315
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:39,320
Now that you're here at school,
who helps your mom with work?

316
00:34:40,257 --> 00:34:42,099
Everyone in my village knows each other.

317
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:43,602
They all help out.

318
00:34:47,977 --> 00:34:51,703
Is everyone in your village Catholic?

319
00:34:53,922 --> 00:34:55,001
Yeah, pretty much.

320
00:35:00,797 --> 00:35:04,801
You know, when my mom found out
I got a scholarship here,

321
00:35:05,666 --> 00:35:07,099
she was over the moon.

322
00:35:14,373 --> 00:35:19,002
People like us don't have many choices.

323
00:35:20,028 --> 00:35:23,204
Just having an ID card
and a place to study

324
00:35:24,826 --> 00:35:28,299
is probably the best choice
we could ask for.

325
00:35:34,860 --> 00:35:36,400
It's the best choice for me too.

326
00:35:48,740 --> 00:35:50,201
They're actually pretty good.

327
00:36:01,690 --> 00:36:04,300
Go on.

328
00:36:04,630 --> 00:36:05,700
Run!

329
00:36:55,386 --> 00:36:57,195
Where the hell are my headphones?

330
00:36:58,087 --> 00:37:00,401
Hey, have you seen my headphones?

331
00:37:00,640 --> 00:37:01,640
You.

332
00:37:11,041 --> 00:37:12,398
Did you take my headphones?

333
00:37:13,897 --> 00:37:15,337
What the hell are you talking about?

334
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:18,496
The headphones
you pulled out of my locker.

335
00:37:21,312 --> 00:37:22,604
I put everything over there.

336
00:37:23,124 --> 00:37:24,297
You took them yourself.

337
00:37:25,390 --> 00:37:26,902
Well, now they're gone.

338
00:37:29,210 --> 00:37:31,002
What the hell does that
have to do with me?

339
00:37:31,158 --> 00:37:32,703
Hey, asshole, watch your mouth.

340
00:37:32,997 --> 00:37:34,500
I'm talking nicely to you.

341
00:37:34,706 --> 00:37:36,400
Are you messing with me? Huh?

342
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:38,497
You don't wanna mess with me.

343
00:37:40,626 --> 00:37:43,250
I've been here forever,
and nothing ever went missing.

344
00:37:43,752 --> 00:37:45,801
Then you show up, and now my stuff's gone.

345
00:37:46,219 --> 00:37:47,219
Asshole.

346
00:37:47,390 --> 00:37:48,834
Watch how you talk to me.

347
00:37:49,739 --> 00:37:51,536
What the hell does your stuff
have to do with me?

348
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:53,602
- Oh, you wanna run your mouth?
- That's right.

349
00:37:53,750 --> 00:37:54,961
What the hell does that
have to do with me?

350
00:37:54,985 --> 00:37:56,185
You wanna run your mouth? Huh?

351
00:37:59,235 --> 00:38:01,500
Barth! Barth! Barth! Stop!

352
00:38:02,088 --> 00:38:02,625
Kongkit!

353
00:38:03,047 --> 00:38:04,197
Or you'll get expelled.

354
00:38:06,613 --> 00:38:09,398
If you don't stop,
you're both getting suspended.

355
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:14,300
He accused me of stealing his stuff.
I didn't steal anything.

356
00:38:14,340 --> 00:38:15,697
- He took my headphones!
- Hey!

357
00:38:16,710 --> 00:38:17,903
I said stop!

358
00:38:18,635 --> 00:38:21,795
Kongkit, who said you could use
headphones here?

359
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:29,002
You, go. You too.

360
00:38:30,890 --> 00:38:32,497
Snapping at each other like dogs.

361
00:38:36,303 --> 00:38:37,977
Go. Everyone, break it up.

362
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:14,400
Barth. What's up?

363
00:39:14,680 --> 00:39:15,702
Looking for something?

364
00:39:16,730 --> 00:39:19,204
My desk's been searched. My bag's gone.

365
00:39:25,154 --> 00:39:26,201
Your bag?

366
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:30,598
I saw… someone take it.

367
00:39:31,545 --> 00:39:32,545
Who?

368
00:39:33,979 --> 00:39:34,979
Who?

369
00:39:35,425 --> 00:39:36,425
Kongkit.

370
00:39:36,887 --> 00:39:37,887
Where did he go?

371
00:39:38,580 --> 00:39:40,100
He went toward the back of the school.

372
00:39:50,742 --> 00:39:51,742
Damn it.

373
00:40:11,760 --> 00:40:12,760
Kongkit!

374
00:40:16,490 --> 00:40:17,490
Kongkit!

375
00:40:21,930 --> 00:40:23,200
Where the hell is he?

376
00:40:25,130 --> 00:40:26,496
Kongkit, come out!

377
00:40:31,374 --> 00:40:32,374
Shit.

378
00:40:36,847 --> 00:40:38,502
Kongkit! Where are you, asshole?

379
00:40:40,108 --> 00:40:41,108
Come out!

380
00:40:48,050 --> 00:40:49,197
Shit.

381
00:41:07,924 --> 00:41:09,496
Shit! You went big, huh?

382
00:41:27,746 --> 00:41:28,746
Shit.

383
00:41:46,136 --> 00:41:49,497
Barth, what are you doing?

384
00:41:52,832 --> 00:41:53,832
Nothing.

385
00:42:02,032 --> 00:42:03,297
Want me to call Master?

386
00:42:08,130 --> 00:42:09,497
I said it's nothing.

387
00:42:09,980 --> 00:42:11,398
Just go back. Stay out of it.

388
00:42:11,622 --> 00:42:12,622
I'll handle it myself.

389
00:42:28,450 --> 00:42:29,703
I said, stay out of it.

390
00:42:32,604 --> 00:42:34,697
It's okay. Let me help.

391
00:42:45,090 --> 00:42:46,690
Are you gonna run and tell Master again?

392
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:53,976
Well, I wasn't snitching.

393
00:42:54,950 --> 00:42:57,120
I just called him
to stop you guys from fighting.

394
00:43:04,669 --> 00:43:07,404
I thought you were gonna tell them
I stole Kongkit's headphones.

395
00:43:12,496 --> 00:43:16,840
I know you didn't steal them.

396
00:43:17,770 --> 00:43:21,099
During free time, I saw you
playing basketball the whole time.

397
00:43:22,990 --> 00:43:24,598
When would you have stolen them?

398
00:43:49,190 --> 00:43:51,303
No one believes someone like me anyway.

399
00:43:54,604 --> 00:43:55,604
Hey.

400
00:43:57,320 --> 00:44:01,977
What's right is always right,
no matter who says it.

401
00:44:05,442 --> 00:44:07,650
Go preach somewhere else. I'm not a baby.

402
00:44:17,760 --> 00:44:18,760
Shit!

403
00:44:24,191 --> 00:44:25,598
Damn it, Kongkit!

404
00:44:32,970 --> 00:44:34,099
How is it, Barth?

405
00:44:37,160 --> 00:44:39,598
There's no other way out.
Everything's locked.

406
00:44:43,174 --> 00:44:45,499
Then stay here with me tonight.

407
00:44:46,096 --> 00:44:47,697
Someone will probably find us.

408
00:44:49,862 --> 00:44:50,862
When?

409
00:44:52,348 --> 00:44:53,348
Morning, I guess.

410
00:45:00,260 --> 00:45:04,200
If Master Phak checks
and we're both missing,

411
00:45:04,654 --> 00:45:05,654
we're so dead.

412
00:45:07,832 --> 00:45:10,800
I'll tell Master I got stuck here
and you came to help me.

413
00:45:11,030 --> 00:45:12,190
You didn't do anything wrong.

414
00:45:16,980 --> 00:45:18,099
Relax.

415
00:45:19,260 --> 00:45:21,460
A good kid like you?
Everyone believes whatever you say.

416
00:45:22,122 --> 00:45:24,797
Me? Who knows what they'll do to me.

417
00:45:30,330 --> 00:45:33,395
You didn't do anything wrong.
I can back you up.

418
00:45:36,352 --> 00:45:37,601
Let's hope that's true.

419
00:45:41,512 --> 00:45:43,699
We should find somewhere to sleep.

420
00:45:43,805 --> 00:45:45,299
No one's finding us now.

421
00:45:52,945 --> 00:45:57,610
What's right is always right,
no matter who says it.

422
00:46:00,813 --> 00:46:02,570
Let's see if what you said is true.

423
00:46:03,903 --> 00:46:05,503
You really love talking back, don't you?

424
00:46:16,666 --> 00:46:17,997
Are you sleeping here?

425
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:23,001
Don't. There's a lot of bat poop up there.

426
00:46:28,060 --> 00:46:29,097
Are you asleep yet?

427
00:46:31,069 --> 00:46:32,069
Yes.

428
00:46:35,357 --> 00:46:38,303
Why do you think this pool was abandoned?

429
00:46:41,985 --> 00:46:43,600
I said I'm asleep.

430
00:46:45,880 --> 00:46:47,299
Then how are you answering me?

431
00:47:10,189 --> 00:47:11,296
You really wanna know?

432
00:47:12,783 --> 00:47:15,404
I don't think you do.

433
00:47:20,161 --> 00:47:21,598
Are you trying to scare me?

434
00:47:30,801 --> 00:47:31,971
You asked for it.

435
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:43,000
This place used to be where…

436
00:47:46,773 --> 00:47:48,103
they would use…

437
00:47:50,970 --> 00:47:51,630
See that mark?

438
00:47:51,651 --> 00:47:52,651
Hey!

439
00:47:55,320 --> 00:47:56,896
You can tell me tomorrow.

440
00:48:06,376 --> 00:48:07,402
Don't be scared.

441
00:48:08,831 --> 00:48:10,250
God is protecting us.

442
00:48:16,478 --> 00:48:18,050
You believe in ghosts too?

443
00:48:20,179 --> 00:48:21,179
No.

444
00:48:22,100 --> 00:48:23,499
When people die,

445
00:48:24,242 --> 00:48:27,699
they either go to heaven
or wait for judgment.

446
00:48:36,290 --> 00:48:37,290
Tanrak.

447
00:48:40,120 --> 00:48:41,401
I'm seriously asking you.

448
00:48:44,348 --> 00:48:46,160
Do you really believe in God?

449
00:48:52,971 --> 00:48:57,600
Like, do you truly believe…
wholeheartedly?

450
00:49:05,750 --> 00:49:07,397
I believe God is real.

451
00:49:09,797 --> 00:49:15,200
I believe my parents are with Him…

452
00:49:19,825 --> 00:49:20,897
up there.

453
00:49:29,910 --> 00:49:31,296
You really believe that?

454
00:49:35,210 --> 00:49:36,754
If you have enough faith,

455
00:49:38,291 --> 00:49:40,099
you'll feel His presence yourself.

456
00:50:03,554 --> 00:50:04,554
You know what?

457
00:50:08,340 --> 00:50:10,102
I used to believe that too.

458
00:50:12,660 --> 00:50:13,660
And then…?

459
00:50:25,980 --> 00:50:27,900
Then one day, I realized

460
00:50:30,589 --> 00:50:34,801
your God never helped me at all.

461
00:50:46,641 --> 00:50:50,804
Maybe my God isn't as kind as yours.

462
00:51:03,139 --> 00:51:04,499
Why do you think that?

463
00:51:13,402 --> 00:51:14,402
Forget it.

464
00:51:16,530 --> 00:51:18,595
I stopped thinking about God
a long time ago.

465
00:51:45,761 --> 00:51:46,899
Hey, come look at this.

466
00:51:48,420 --> 00:51:49,497
Master, over here!

467
00:51:59,380 --> 00:52:01,604
Hey, wake up.

468
00:52:46,710 --> 00:52:48,430
The only wrong thing you did
was to help me,

469
00:52:48,505 --> 00:52:49,804
(Next Episode)
and now you're screwed too.

470
00:52:49,828 --> 00:52:52,804
I think you could've handled
this better, Tanrak.

471
00:52:52,890 --> 00:52:54,130
I'm really sorry, Father.

472
00:52:54,570 --> 00:52:55,797
Can I move over here?

473
00:52:56,139 --> 00:52:58,303
Father made me your buddy.

474
00:52:58,590 --> 00:52:59,696
So you should tutor me.

475
00:52:59,942 --> 00:53:01,170
Why should I tutor you?

476
00:53:01,490 --> 00:53:02,502
Because we're friends.

477
00:53:02,710 --> 00:53:04,700
Since when are we friends? Huh?

478
00:53:06,946 --> 00:53:09,201
Since when are Tan and Barth besties?

479
00:53:09,302 --> 00:53:11,565
Yeah. When did they become close friends?

480
00:53:14,263 --> 00:53:15,998
Can you stop breaking the rules already?

481
00:53:17,097 --> 00:53:18,903
Come with me. I'll help you.
